snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Indians, please don't take this personally, but you really need to stop writing this "we are one" nonsense in every Coke Studio video. We never were ONE, and never will be ONE.

The British came and occupied us in 1845 (after fall of Sindh and Punjab) and forcibly merged us into a fake country called "British India". Only colonialized haramzadeh think that was a real country. Your great grandfathers considered it an occupation! We were occupied from 1845 until 1947. In 1857 we (Muslims) fought back against the British occupation, while you know who decided to cut deals with the British. 95 years of British Indian occupation does not erase over 9000 years of distinct Indus culture....Pakistan inherited that Indus culture in 1947...this Indus culture has merged with Sufism to form Pakistani culture today.

So I'm sorry to break the news to you, but we are "not one". I mean look at the average Pakistani and average Indian and its apparent. Linguistically we are different, culturally we are different, and yes genetically we are different. This has nothing to do with Hinduism or Islam, it has to do with Indus and Gangetic cultures that developed thousands of years ago. North India (Gangetic culture) and Pakistan (Indus culture) have always been separate entities. And always will be.

Peace out.
